Bring a large saucepan of salted water to the boil and cook the trompetti pasta for 10â€“12 minutes, until al dente. Drain the pasta, reserving a little of the cooking water.Meanwhile, heat the oil in a large frying pan over a medium heat. Add the leek and pancetta and sweat for a couple of minutes. Stir in the chestnuts and rosemary and season with salt and pepper. Cover with the lid and cook for 5 minutes.In a bowl, combine the mascarpone with a little of the pasta cooking water to loosen it up slightly. Add the pasta to the chestnut mixture, stir in the mascarpone and mix well, adding a little more reserved cooking water if necessary.Serve with a sprinkling of grated pecorino.